            <h4>How to get there</h4>
            <p>Olongapo City lies 127 kilometers north of Manila, a three- hour drive on the average along the North Luzon Express- way (NLEX) and Subic-
                Clark Tarlac Expressway (SCTEX). The City is located in the southwestern portion of Zambales province. </p>
            <h4>Best time to visit</h4>
            <p>1. Summer season (April-May) – Olongapo is rich in natural water resources such as pristine beaches.</p>
